Mac - python3
Windows - py
To install we need pip: -m pip install
To create a Virtual Enviroment
    1.python3 -m pip virtualenv
         py -m pip virtualenv
    2.python3 -m venv (folder name)
        py -m venv ("venv" - just the name of the folder )
    3. #activate the Virtual Enviroment
      you need to be located in to the folder
        a) source venv/bin/activate  #Mac
        b) venv\Scripts\activate  #Windows
    4. py -m pip install flask